{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba374006-b00b-4cde-8c0d-eac721134891","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main tools you can use:\n\n**`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**`lldb` with SOS** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\n**WinDbg** (Windows) with the SOS extension is another option if you're on Windows.\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your dump file? If so, let me know the path to the `.dmp` file and I can walk through the investigation interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dd86eaec-4b9d-4960-9b7e-8d429d8da297","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says:\n\n\"USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump.\"\n\n\"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing, or for .NET Framework processes.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\n\nI'll provide direct guidance on analyzing the dump file instead, covering the main tools and approaches they can use.","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"5030:11A527:282FB9:328A9D:69F555CB"},"id":"c9b0ff99-2256-4563-8adf-7cc07b8629a0","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01: